<issue
	id="nks-47"
  type="arm"
  linkend="State_definition.State_definition_relationship"
  category="major_technical"
  by="Nigel Shaw"
  date="2002-09-23"
  status="open">
  <description>
	  The several of subtypes of this entity lack context. An Or relationship may only apply in the context of one state_definition but the model does not make it possible to describe the context. Similarly for And and Xor (why is Xor only between two?)
	  It might be better to declare one attribute from State_definition_relationship that points to State_definition and is then renamed. It should act as the parent in all parent-child cases and as the cause in cause-effect cases.
	  In the case of And and OR, it acts as the context(?).
</description>

